Class ConcreteTimeSeries<DATA,TS extends ConcreteTimeSeries<DATA,TS>>

  • java.lang.Object

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    WordDFIDFTimeSeries

    public abstract class ConcreteTimeSeries<DATA,TS extends ConcreteTimeSeries<DATA,TS>>
extends TimeSeries<DATA[],DATA,TS>
implements TimeSeriesCollectionAssignable<DATA,TS>
    A generic though inefficient time series which can be used by any data type. This implementation is backed by a treemap. Array construction is handled using ReflectionUtils.getTypeArguments(Class, Class). To use this class simple define a new class
    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • get

        public TS get(long time,
              int nbefore,
              int nafter)
        Description copied from class: TimeSeries
        returns the DATA at a specific point in time and those before and after to the number requested. This method may not return data for the specific requested time if it does not exists. If the time series is completely empty this function may return at an empty array however if at least 1 data point exists and either nbefore and nafter are bigger than 1 then at least 1 datapoint will be returned.

        Data should be returned in order

      • get

        public TS get(long time,
              long threshbefore,
              long threshafter)
        Description copied from class: TimeSeries
        returns the RETURNTYPE at a specific point in time and those before and after within the specified thresholds. This method may not return data for the specific requested time if it does not exists. Similarly this method may return an empty array if no time data is available within the window specified.

        Data should be returned in order
